column3: Market Value of U.S. Holdings of Foreign Securities at the End of the Year Shown

column1: Country code
Department of the Treasury/Federal Reserve Board
Treasury International Capital System
https://www.treasury.gov/resource-center/data-chart-center/tic/Pages/index.aspx
*    Greater than zero but less than $500,000.
r    Revised
n.a. Not available.
1.   For 1994 and 1997, totals include only holdings of equity and long-term
debt.  From 2001 onwards, totals include holdings of short-term debt as well as
equity and long-term debt.
2.   Belgium and Luxembourg were combined as Belgium-Luxembourg in the 1994
survey.  From 1997 forward, they were reported separately.
3.   Separate reporting for Anguilla, British Virgin Islands, Cayman Islands,
Montserrat, and Turks and Caicos began with the 1997 survey; previously these
entries were reported as the British West Indies.
4.   Separate reporting for Guernsey and Jersey began with the 1997 survey; in
the 1994 survey these entries were included in the United Kingdom.
5.   Separate reporting for Bonaire, Sint Eustatius, and Saba; Curacao; and
Sint Maarten began with the 2013 survey. In previous years, these entries were
reported together as Netherlands Antilles.
6.   Separate reporting for Guadeloupe and for Saint Martin and Saint
Barthelemy began with the 2013 survey. In previous years, entries for Guadeloupe
included Saint Martin and Saint Barthelemy.
7.   Separate reporting for Kosovo, Montenegro, and Serbia began with the 2013
survey. In previous years, entries for Serbia included Kosovo and Montenegro.
8.   Bahrain, Iran, Iraq, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, United Arab
Emirates.  These countries are reported separately beginning in 2006.
9.   Algeria, Gabon, Libya, Nigeria.   These countries are reported separately
beginning in 2006.
